Senior Pastor of the Redeemed Christian Church of God (RCCG) Jesus House Washington DC Parish, Pastor Afolabi Ghandi Olaoye, has stated his ambition to be the new Soun of Ogbomoso is the will of God. 1. He is a pastor at the Redeemed Christian Church of God, America 2. His parish ‘Jesus House’, Washington DC is the biggest RCCG church in America. 3. He is fondly called ‘Pastor G’ and is known for his servant heart and leadership skills. 4. Pastor Olaoye was born and raised in Nigeria.   Nigeria vs Ghana: Seven things to expect in Qatar 2022…     Train Attack: Family members apprehensive over where-about…     Becoming Soun of Ogbomoso has God’s backing – RGGC…   5. He has a degree in English Language and a Masters in Industrial and Labor Relations. 6. He was a successful entrepreneur before the call of God came upon his life to become a Pastor. 7. He has been a Pastor since 1992. 8. He pastored three RCCG Churches in Nigeria, an RCCG Parish in Bonn, Germany before moving to the United States. 9. He is the coordinator in charge of Convention and Special Projects for RCCG, North America. 10. He is happily married to Pastor Omo, who also played a key role in running the affair of the church. 11. His wife is the founder and Pastor in charge of the Jesus Women Ministries, a women’s ministry that addresses pertinent women’s issues from birth to old age, with a view to positively affecting these areas in line with the Word of God.